description: Teriyaki-flavoured eggplant takes this fried rice recipe to an irresistible level. Try this easy recipe for a speedy weeknight dinner.
keywords: Fried rice,Eggplant,Low saturated fat,Seafood free,Healthier Easier,Weeknight dinner,Low sugar,Budget,Fakeaway,Quick & easy dinner,High protein,High fibre,Wheat free,Rice,Jan Feb 2021
name: Teriyaki Eggplant Fried Rice Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 450g frozen steam fresh beans, broccoli & sugar snaps

recipeInstructions.text: Heat 2 tsp oil in a wok or large frying pan over high heat. Add eggs and swirl to coat pan in a thin layer. Cook for 2 minutes or until set and golden underneath. Transfer to a plate. When cool enough to handle, roll into a log and thinly slice.
Heat remaining oil in wok or large frying pan over high heat. Stir-fry eggplant for 5 minutes or until golden and tender.
Meanwhile, place frozen vegetables in a medium heatproof bowl. Pour over boiling water to cover and stand for 3 minutes. Drain.

Add drained vegetables and rice to wok. Stir-fry for 2 minutes or until heated through. Add sauce and stir-fry for 1 minute or until coated and heated through. Stir in half the onion and half the egg. Serve topped with remaining egg and onion, and sesame seeds.
